# Admire Admin Project Structure

This rule documents the structure of the Admire Learning Center admin dashboard built with Next.js App Router.

## Core Files

- **Main Entry Point**: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with HTML/body structure
- **Main Redirect**: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Root page that redirects to login
- **Global CSS**: [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global styles and variables

## App Organization

The application follows Next.js App Router structure:

```
src/
  app/ - All pages and layouts
    api/ - Backend API routes
    dashboard/ - Admin dashboard pages
      layout.tsx - Dashboard layout with Sidebar and Header
      page.tsx - Main dashboard statistics page
      settings/ - Settings section
    login/ - Authentication pages
  components/ - Reusable React components
```

## Authentication Flow

1. Users start at [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) and are redirected to login
2. Login page is rendered by [src/app/login/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/login/page.tsx)
3. Authentication API at [src/app/api/login/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/login/route.ts)
4. Upon success, users are redirected to [src/app/dashboard/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/dashboard/page.tsx)

## Components

Shared components are stored in [src/components/](mdc:src/components/):

- **Header**: [src/components/Header.tsx](mdc:src/components/Header.tsx) - Top navigation
- **Sidebar**: [src/components/Sidebar.tsx](mdc:src/components/Sidebar.tsx) - Dashboard sidebar navigation

## Page Structure

Each dashboard page follows a common structure:

1. Main content wrapped in dashboard layout
2. Cards for statistics and data display
3. Consistent styling following the [style guide](mdc:.cursor/rules/style-guide.mdc)
